children.label: spaces

children.label: actions

children.label: options

interfaces.label: CheckAuthorizationResult
description:
The CheckAuthorizationResult interface contains the overall status of an
authorization check and the specific authorized privileges as an
AuthorizationTypeMap.

children.label: status
description:
The overall status of the authorization check as a string:
'fully_authorized' | 'partially_authorized' | 'unauthorized'

children.label: typeMap

The specific authorized privileges: a map of type to record

interfaces.label: EncryptedObjectDescriptor
description:
The EncryptedObjectDescriptor interface contains settings for describing
an object to be encrypted or decrpyted.

children.label: type
description: The Saved Object type

children.label: id
description: The Saved Object ID

children.label: namespace
description:
Namespace for use in index migration...
If the object is being decrypted during index migration, the object was previously
encrypted with its namespace in the descriptor portion of the AAD; on the other hand,
if the object is being decrypted during object migration, the object was never encrypted
with its namespace in the descriptor portion of the AAD.

children.label: auditCallback

A callback intended to handle adding audit events in
both error (unauthorized), or success (authorized)
cases

interfaces.label: ISavedObjectsEncryptionExtension
description:
The ISavedObjectsEncryptionExtension interface defines the functions of a saved objects
repository encryption extension. It contains functions for determining if a type is
encryptable, encrypting object attributes, and decrypting or stripping object attributes.

children.label: isEncryptableType
description: Returns true if a type has been registered as encryptable.

children.label: type
description: - the string name of the object type

returnComment: boolean, true if type is encryptable

children.label: decryptOrStripResponseAttributes
description:
Given a saved object, will return a decrypted saved object or will strip
attributes from the returned object if decryption fails.

children.label: response
description: - any object R that extends SavedObject with attributes T

children.label: originalAttributes
description:
- optional, original attributes T from when the object was created (NOT encrypted).
These are used to avoid decryption execution cost if they are supplied.

returnComment: R with decrypted or stripped attributes

children.label: encryptAttributes
description:
Given a saved object descriptor and some attributes, returns an encrypted version
of supplied attributes.

children.label: descriptor
description: - an object containing a saved object id, type, and optional namespace.

children.label: attributes
description: - T, attributes of the specified object, some of which to be encrypted.

children.label: exportByObjects

interfaces.label: ISavedObjectsSecurityExtension
description:
The ISavedObjectsSecurityExtension interface defines the functions of a saved objects repository security extension.
It contains functions for checking & enforcing authorization, adding audit events, and redacting namespaces.

children.label: performAuthorization
description: Performs authorization (check & enforce) of actions on specified types in specified spaces.

children.label: params
description: - actions, types & spaces map, audit callback, options (enforce bypassed if enforce map is undefined)

returnComment: CheckAuthorizationResult - the resulting authorization level and authorization map

children.label: enforceAuthorization
description:
Enforces authorization of a single action on specified types in specified spaces.
Throws error if authorization map does not cover specified parameters.

children.label: params
description: - map of types/spaces, action to check, and authz map (from CheckAuthorizationResult)

children.label: addAuditEvent
description: Adds an audit event for the specified action with relevant information

children.label: params
description: - the action, outcome, error, and relevant object/space information

children.label: redactNamespaces
description: Filters a saved object's spaces based on an authorization map (from CheckAuthorizationResult)

children.label: params
description: - the saved object and an authorization map

returnComment: SavedObject - saved object with filtered spaces

interfaces.label: ISavedObjectsSpacesExtension
description:
The ISavedObjectsSpacesExtension interface defines the functions of a saved objects repository spaces extension.
It contains functions for getting the current namespace & getting and array of searchable spaces.

children.label: getCurrentNamespace
description:
Retrieves the active namespace ID. This is *not* the same as a namespace string. See also: `namespaceIdToString` and
`namespaceStringToId`.

This takes the saved objects repository's namespace option as a parameter, and doubles as a validation function; if the namespace
option has already been set some other way, this will throw an error.

children.label: getSearchableNamespaces
description:
Given a list of namespace strings, returns a subset that the user is authorized to search in.
If a wildcard '*' is used, it is expanded to an explicit list of namespace strings.

interfaces.label: ISavedObjectTypeRegistry
description: Registry holding information about all the registered {@link SavedObjectsType | saved object types}.

description: Return the {@link SavedObjectsType | type} definition for given type name.

Returns all visible {@link SavedObjectsType | types}.

children.label: getAllTypes

children.label: getImportableAndExportableTypes

children.label: isMultiNamespace

children.label: isShareable

Returns whether the type is multi-namespace (shareable);
resolves to `false` if the type is not registered

interfaces.label: SavedObjectMigrationMap
description:
A map of {@link SavedObjectMigrationFn | migration functions} to be used for a given type.
The map's keys must be valid semver versions, and they cannot exceed the current Kibana version.

For a given document, only migrations with a higher version number than that of the document will be applied.
Migrations are executed in order, starting from the lowest version and ending with the highest one.

interfaces.label: SavedObjectsServiceSetup

Saved Objects is Kibana's data persistence mechanism allowing plugins to
use Elasticsearch for storing and querying state. The SavedObjectsServiceSetup API exposes methods
or registering Saved Object types, and creating and registering Saved Object client factories.

Saved Objects is Kibana's data persistence mechanism allowing plugins to
use Elasticsearch for storing and querying state. The
SavedObjectsServiceStart API provides a scoped Saved Objects client for

Creates a {@link SavedObjectsClientContract | Saved Objects client} that

children.label: extensions

interfaces.label: SavedObjectStatusMeta
description: Meta information about the SavedObjectService's status. Available to plugins via {@link CoreSetup.status}.

children.label: migratedIndices
signature: { [status: string]: number; skipped: number; migrated: number; }

children.label: name
description: The name of the type, which is also used as the internal id.

children.label: hidden
description:
Is the type hidden by default. If true, repositories will not have access to this type unless explicitly
declared as an `extraType` when creating the repository.
It is recommended to hide the type for better backward compatibility.
The hidden types will not be automatically exposed via the HTTP API.
Therefore, that should prevent unexpected behavior in the client code, as all the interactions will be done via the plugin API.

See {@link SavedObjectsServiceStart.createInternalRepository | createInternalRepository}.

children.label: namespaceType
description: The {@link SavedObjectsNamespaceType | namespace type} for the type.

children.label: indexPattern
description: If defined, the type instances will be stored in the given index instead of the default one.

children.label: convertToAliasScript
description: If defined, will be used to convert the type to an alias.

children.label: excludeOnUpgrade
description:
If defined, allows a type to exclude unneeded documents from the migration process and effectively be deleted.
See {@link SavedObjectTypeExcludeFromUpgradeFilterHook} for more details.

children.label: mappings
description: The {@link SavedObjectsTypeMappingDefinition | mapping definition} for the type.

children.label: migrations
description: An optional map of {@link SavedObjectMigrationFn | migrations} or a function returning a map of {@link SavedObjectMigrationFn | migrations} to be used to migrate the type.

children.label: schemas
description:
An optional schema that can be used to validate the attributes of the type.

When provided, calls to {@link SavedObjectsClient.create | create} will be validated against this schema.

See {@link SavedObjectsValidationMap} for more details.

children.label: convertToMultiNamespaceTypeVersion
description:
If defined, objects of this type will be converted to a 'multiple' or 'multiple-isolated' namespace type when migrating to this
version.

Requirements:

 1. This string value must be a valid semver version
 2. This type must have previously specified {@link SavedObjectsNamespaceType | `namespaceType: 'single'`}
 3. This type must also specify {@link SavedObjectsNamespaceType | `namespaceType: 'multiple'`} *or*
    {@link SavedObjectsNamespaceType | `namespaceType: 'multiple-isolated'`}

Example of a single-namespace type in 7.12:

```ts
{
  name: 'foo',
  hidden: false,
  namespaceType: 'single',
  mappings: {...}
}
```

Example after converting to a multi-namespace (isolated) type in 8.0:

```ts
{
  name: 'foo',
  hidden: false,
  namespaceType: 'multiple-isolated',
  mappings: {...},
  convertToMultiNamespaceTypeVersion: '8.0.0'
}
```

Example after converting to a multi-namespace (shareable) type in 8.1:

```ts
{
  name: 'foo',
  hidden: false,
  namespaceType: 'multiple',
  mappings: {...},
  convertToMultiNamespaceTypeVersion: '8.0.0'
}
```

Note: migration function(s) can be optionally specified for any of these versions and will not interfere with the conversion process.

children.label: management
description: An optional {@link SavedObjectsTypeManagementDefinition | saved objects management section} definition for the type.

interfaces.label: SavedObjectsTypeManagementDefinition
description: Configuration options for the {@link SavedObjectsType | type}'s management section.

children.label: importableAndExportable
description: Is the type importable or exportable. Defaults to `false`.

children.label: displayName
description: When specified, will be used instead of the type's name in SO management section's labels.

children.label: visibleInManagement
description:
When set to false, the type will not be listed or searchable in the SO management section.
Main usage of setting this property to false for a type is when objects from the type should
be included in the export via references or export hooks, but should not directly appear in the SOM.
Defaults to `true`.

children.label: defaultSearchField
description: The default search field to use for this type. Defaults to `id`.

children.label: icon
description:
The eui icon name to display in the management table.
If not defined, the default icon will be used.

children.label: getTitle
description:
Function returning the title to display in the management table.
If not defined, will use the object's type and id to generate a label.

children.label: getEditUrl
description:
Function returning the url to use to redirect to the editing page of this object.
If not defined, editing will not be allowed.

children.label: getInAppUrl
description:
Function returning the url to use to redirect to this object from the management section.
If not defined, redirecting to the object will not be allowed.
returnComment:
an object containing a `path` and `uiCapabilitiesPath` properties. the `path` is the path to
the object page, relative to the base path. `uiCapabilitiesPath` is the path to check in the
{@link Capabilities | uiCapabilities} to check if the user has permission to access the object.

children.label: onExport
description:
An optional export transform function that can be used transform the objects of the registered type during
the export process.

It can be used to either mutate the exported objects, or add additional objects (of any type) to the export list.

See {@link SavedObjectsExportTransform | the transform type documentation} for more info and examples.

When implementing both `isExportable` and `onExport`, it is mandatory that
`isExportable` returns the same value for an object before and after going
though the export transform.
E.g `isExportable(objectBeforeTransform) === isExportable(objectAfterTransform)`

children.label: onImport
description:
An optional {@link SavedObjectsImportHook | import hook} to use when importing given type.

Import hooks are executed during the savedObjects import process and allow to interact
with the imported objects. See the {@link SavedObjectsImportHook | hook documentation}
for more info.

children.label: isExportable
description:
Optional hook to specify whether an object should be exportable.

If specified, `isExportable` will be called during export for each
of this type's objects in the export, and the ones not matching the
predicate will be excluded from the export.

When implementing both `isExportable` and `onExport`, it is mandatory that
`isExportable` returns the same value for an object before and after going
though the export transform.
E.g `isExportable(objectBeforeTransform) === isExportable(objectAfterTransform)`

interfaces.label: SavedObjectsTypeMappingDefinition
description: Describe a saved object type mapping.

children.label: dynamic
description:
The dynamic property of the mapping, either `false` or `'strict'`. If
unspecified `dynamic: 'strict'` will be inherited from the top-level
index mappings.

children.label: properties

interfaces.label: SavedObjectsValidationMap
description:
A map of {@link SavedObjectsValidationSpec | validation specs} to be used for a given type.
The map's keys must be valid semver versions.

Any time you change the schema of a {@link SavedObjectsType}, you should add a new entry
to this map for the Kibana version the change was introduced in.

misc.label: SavedObjectsExportTransform
description:
Transformation function used to mutate the exported objects of the associated type.

A type's export transform function will be executed once per user-initiated export,
for all objects of that type.

misc.label: SavedObjectsExtensionFactory
description: Describes the base Saved Objects Extension factory.

misc.label: SavedObjectsFieldMapping
SavedObjectsImportHook
description:
A hook associated with a specific saved object type, that will be invoked during
the import process. The hook will have access to the objects of the registered type.

Currently, the only supported feature for import hooks is to return warnings to be displayed
in the UI when the import succeeds.

misc.label: SavedObjectsSecurityExtensionFactory
description: Describes the factory used to create instances of the Saved Objects Security Extension.

misc.label: SavedObjectsSpacesExtensionFactory
description: Describes the factory used to create instances of the Saved Objects Spaces Extension.

misc.label: SavedObjectsValidationSpec
description: Allows for validating properties using @kbn/config-schema validations.

misc.label: SavedObjectTypeExcludeFromUpgradeFilterHook
description:
If defined, allows a type to run a search query and return a query filter that may match any documents which may
be excluded from the next migration upgrade process. Useful for cleaning up large numbers of old documents which
are no longer needed and may slow the migration process.

If this hook fails, the migration will proceed without these documents having been filtered out, so this
should not be used as a guarantee that these documents have been deleted.

misc.label: SavedObjectUnsanitizedDoc
description:
Describes Saved Object documents from Kibana < 7.0.0 which don't have a
`references` root property defined. This type should only be used in
migrations.
